bridle track
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a path or track for horses, the preferred NZ 19C. use, and still extant, a track fit or designed only for horse rather than wheeled traffic.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [nf OED2; EDD 1879 Wiltshire, (1890) Scotland); W3]
